The goal of the video analysis layer is to help detect badminton active rallies vs dead intervals.

Start simple:
- Do not use AI/ML models yet.
- Do not use audio in v1.
- Do not attempt shuttle detection in v1.
- First compute visual motion score using sampled frames.

Motion analysis v1:
- Read frames using OpenCV.
- Sample frames at a configurable interval, such as every 0.5 seconds.
- Resize frames before comparison for speed.
- Convert frames to grayscale.
- Compute absolute difference between consecutive sampled frames.
- Normalize the motion score so it is easy to compare across videos.
- Return one motion score per sampled timestamp.

Important:
- Make the algorithm easy to debug.
- Return intermediate signal data instead of only final labels.
- Prefer inspectable values over black-box logic.
- Later, detected active/dead segments should be derived from motionSeries using thresholds and smoothing.

Future ideas, but do not implement unless asked:
- Court ROI selection
- Audio energy timeline
- Optical flow
- Pose detection
- Custom AI model
- User correction / labeling workflow